caption: The courtyard of the city hall was the main fan zone of the Paris Olympics 2024. The temporary fan zone was a nice contrast between the new and the old surroundings. The fan zone was full of joy, fun, there were water fountains everywhere and seats to sit down and enjoy the sport. There were people around if you wanted to ask questions about the Olympics or places to eat around the area. The fan zone may not be there when you read this review but the Courtyard will be and it's a beautiful structure üòä

The 2024 Olympics had a free viewing area here. It was a great spot to watch the games, mingle with other spectators, and enjoy the neighborhood. There are also a few metro stops within walking distance.
Visited right after the Olympic games ended. They still had the area set up with Olympic inspired activities to play. It was fun to stop in and see and grab some Olympics swag

Lovely to visit for the holidays, magical decorations, and also a lot of activities for everyone, like climbing, sledding or riding a carousel, all free of charge. A lot of fun for all ages. The snacks and drinks also very good!
superbly beautiful building, currently a fanzone for the 2024 Paris Olympics

Les Toqu√©s de L'agriculture, a food, wine and agricultural products show was held here April 29, 30 and May 1, 2022. Entrance was free and so were many cheese, wine, bread and charcuterie samples. Each region of France was represented by a booth where products were available for purchase and various sampling platters were available for a very reasonable cost as well as cider and wine. The organization seemed flawless and the setup made for an enjoyable afternoon learning about French food. Facilities included compost toilets, covered dining area and live kitchen demonstrations on the central stage. Congratulations to the organizers and staff for an impressive event.
